When you deploy to Vercel, you need to add the following Environment Variables in your Vercel project settings (under Settings > Environment Variables).

Here is exactly what you should add:

1. NEXT_PUBLIC_POCKETBASE_URL
Value: The live URL of your hosted PocketBase server (e.g., https://chitra-db.pockethost.io)
Description: This tells your Next.js app where to find the database instead of looking for localhost:8090.
2. NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME
Value: Chitra
Description: The name of your application.
3. NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_SECRET
Value: A long, random, and secure string (e.g., super_secret_encryption_key_for_chitra_1234567890)
Description: This is used for encrypting the end-to-end communication on the canvas. Make sure to generate a strong, random password-like string for your production environment and keep it secret.
Once you add these three variables, Vercel will automatically inject them into your app during the build process, and your application will go live successfully!